{"id": 11630, "date": "1987-04-16T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-04-16T18:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=11630"}, "modified": "2026-06-10T15:14:18", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T22:14:18", "slug": "matr-pete-seeger-and-bruce-springsteen-goodnight-irene", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/04/16/matr-pete-seeger-and-bruce-springsteen-goodnight-irene/", "title": {"rendered": "Goodnight, Irene"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>No one knows for sure quite when or where it started, but we know that Lead Belly was the first to record it: In 1933, he released the first recorded version of &#8220;Goodnight, Irene,&#8221; and it went on to become not just one of Lead Belly&#8217;s most popular songs but a bonafide American folk standard.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a recording that dates back to 1943, when it was already quite popular:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NT-OuWmXDsY?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>As for the Bruce connection, that comes via Pete Seeger&#8217;s cover in 1950 with The Weavers:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MSDyiUBrUSk?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bruce has performed &#8220;Goodnight, Irene&#8221; twice, although an argument could be made about whether either should &#8220;count.&#8221;</p>\n<p>The first time was at Pete Seeger&#8217;s 90th birthday concert at Madison Square Garden, on the evening of May 3, 2009. The assembled artists (and there were <em>many, </em>Bruce and Patti included) re-assembled at the end of the night for a final encore of &#8220;Goodnight, Irene.&#8221;</p>\n<p>But neither Bruce nor Patti were anywhere near the microphone, so while we can clearly see them singing, we&#8217;ll have to take it on faith that their voices are somewhere deep down in the mix.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Jo-1ybxwFc4?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bruce&#8217;s second attempt came a few years later, at London&#8217;s Hyde Park, as an improvised &#8220;good night&#8221; when the venue cut the power after Bruce and Sir Paul McCartney(!) finished &#8220;Twist and Shout.&#8221;</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s only a single chorus, and it&#8217;s probably the lowest (no-est?) energy Springsteen encore ever, but it made for a unique and memorable ending to an even more memorable show.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/OqbLFWZd4CI?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Because the power had been cut, only those near the stage (or the engineers monitoring the feed above) could hear it&#8211;by strange coincidence making &#8220;Goodnight, Irene&#8221; a song that Bruce has &#8220;officially&#8221; covered more than once but which almost no one in the venue could hear.</p>\n<p><strong>Goodnight, Irene</strong><br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> May 3, 2009 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> July 14, 2012 (London, England)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 August 1, 2019</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>By remarkable circumstance, Bruce covered &#8220;Goodnight, Irene&#8221; in concert twice, but almost no one in the venue heard him! You can, though&#8211;watch the great video inside.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69876, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [2420, 2421, 172], "class_list": ["post-11630", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-goodnight-irene", "tag-lead-belly", "tag-pete-seeger"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/admin-ajax-2026-06-10T151218.492.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-31A", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 57722, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/07/14/kingdom-of-days-july-14-2/", "url_meta": {"origin": 11630, "position": 0}, "title": "July 14", "author": "Ken", "date": "July 14, 2025", "format": false, "excerpt": "On this date: Bruce and Paul McCartney learn what happens when you break curfew at Hyde Park.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Kingdom of Days&quot;", "block_context": {"text": "Kingdom of Days", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/category/kingdom-of-days/"}, "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/brucepaul-1.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200, "srcset": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/brucepaul-1.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200 1x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/brucepaul-1.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&ssl=1&resize=525%2C300 1.5x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/brucepaul-1.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&ssl=1&resize=700%2C400 2x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/brucepaul-1.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&ssl=1&resize=1050%2C600 3x"}, "classes": []}, {"id": 27626, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/09/09/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-r